social_posts.post_text: I’ve always worked behind the scenes for @mrbobbybones but today he handed me a hot mic and let me chat with @joeylogano! We talked about the Nashville Fairgrounds, rookie driver initiations, making amends after on track incidents and more. Full interview is up on the @bobbybonesshow YT channel 🏁

This year marks a decade of working with @mrbobbybones which is hard to wrap my brain around. Ten years ago, I was a college student working extra jobs just so I could afford the gas to get from Murfreesboro to the morning show to intern for free. Bobby took me under his wing and believed in me enough to tell the people that did the hiring to believe in me too. And the rest, as they say, is history. I’m so proud to be a part of the team all these years later and can’t wait to see him crush it at the GRAMMYs red carpet 👊🏻

MDS6 is in the books! So grateful for the artists that took time out of their schedules to come play, to the team of all stars that helped put it together, to everyone that bought a ticket to raise money for St Jude, and to Bobby for letting me have the coolest job ever 🤍

Every time I step foot in the Ryman, I think of my pawpaw who was a preacher, radio host and gospel singer. He passed away in a car accident when I was young, but a few years ago my dad told me he always had a dream to perform on the Grand Ole Opry at the Ryman. This week I helped execute a show at the venue he dreamed of playing and the Opry team was on site to tape it. I like to think these things don’t just happen. Something tells me pawpaw had the best seat in the house Tuesday night ⛪️ 🤍
Always easy to celebrate @nikitakarmen. Y’all go stream her new album Fantasy Island! There’s a rumor that “Next Round” is loosely based off of my love life. I can neither confirm or deny
We proceeded to cry our eyes out on the carousel and ride it 27 more times 🥹 🎠
Serotonin boosted 📈🥹 #auntlife

I was excited each morning to roll out of bed at 5am to get going and that’s saying something! (Scroll to Slide 4 to see a live action shot of @ktdortch and I rolling up to the river every morning)

Hit one hundo at @rumbleboxinggulch today. A year ago I wasn’t working out at all and knew I needed to work on self-discipline, but was lacking the confidence to get started. A friend invited me to my first class…I remember the anxiety I had walking in. But it turns out I really like throwing hands 🤣 proud of me today! 🫶🥊

Today I said goodbye to a car that I’ve lived a lot of life in. Bought her brand new when I graduated college. I remember being so nervous making my first “big girl” purchase and hoping I wouldn’t regret it. When I handed over the keys today she had nearly 150k miles. So much life and so many memories made. Feels silly to be sentimental over a car, but I got a little teary on my last drive. I hope her next owner loves her as much as I did ♥️
My A1 since Day 1 @meaganteddleton #twins #twinsisters

On Tuesday 11/7 I was able to hold my sister’s hand as she brought my nephew Dawson into the world and I felt my heart stretch! When Meg was pregnant with Cooper a few years ago, I decided then that I would do my absolute best to be a present and steady figure in her children’s lives. Not just an aunt they’d see at an annual family get together, but an aunt that gets on a plane on an off weekend to go watch a tee ball game and binge all the Spy Kids movies (because we have to pass on the classics 🤣) Being an aunt has been one of my greatest joys and I’m so excited to welcome Dawson into our family and get to know him as he grows up 🥹
Little sleep and lots of love to end 2023 on 🤍 Looking forward to some new adventures in 24!
